label.value: Complete heart block with broad QRS complexes

definition.value: A type of third degree heart block in which the escape rhythm arises at a relatively low part of the conduction system (below the atrioventricular node), which produces a wide QRS complex.

label.value: Complete heart block with narrow QRS complexes

definition.value: A type of third degree heart block in which the escape rhythm arises at the atrioventricular node, which produces a narrow QRS complex.

label.value: Aplasia of the abdominal wall musculature

definition.value: A congenital malformation characterized by the development of an additional organ or organ-like structure, i.e., an extra copy of the organ normally located in the abdomen.
